# Category Language

## Purpose

This section tracks working language for describing the thesis and EWS without forcing one phrase to do every job.

## Recommended language stack

### Internal doctrine

Bounded operational trust layer

### Master-document anchor

Governed interpretation layer

### Functional product description

Operational drift qualification layer

### Simple outward explanation

Operational interpretation system

### Supporting phrase

Signal credibility layer

## Current recommendation

Use a layered phrasing model rather than choosing one universal label.

The deepest thesis language does not need to be the same as the simplest outward-facing description.

## Terms to avoid as primary labels

- copilot
- agent platform
- autonomous operations
- generic observability
- broad AI assistant
- generalized intelligence

## Drafting notes

Category language should protect the control point, not inflate the project.
